What does the DOM stand for, and why is it important for test automation?

The full form of DOM is Document Object Model
The DOM is a structure of a webpage that allows programs (like JavaScript or automation tools) to see and interact with elements.
It is important for automation because 
  1. It helps locate elements. 
  2. Using Dom we can interact with elements like enter text or click buttons
  3. It can validate results (visibility of elements etc.,)


